==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lorica
<hw>Lo*ri"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Loric⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., lit., a corselet of
thongs, fr. <ets>lorum</ets> thong.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anc.
Armor)</fld> <def>A cuirass, originally of leather, afterward of plates
of metal or horn sewed on linen or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Lute{1} for protecting vessels
from the fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The protective case or shell of
an infusorian or rotifer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loricata</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
